casebody.data:
William C. HENRY v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 7539. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Nov. 14, 1938. Alvord & Alvord and Floyd F. Toomey, all of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. James W. Morris, Sewall Key, and Herman Oliphant, all of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed pursuant to motion of petitioner.
